Class ExecutorExtension<E extends Executor>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.servicetalk.concurrent.api.ExecutorExtension<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of Executor.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.AfterAllCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.AfterEachCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.BeforeAllCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.BeforeEachCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.Extension
    public final class ExecutorExtension<E extends Executor>
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.AfterEachCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.BeforeEachCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.AfterAllCallback, org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.BeforeAllCallback
    An Extension wrapper that creates and disposes an Executor for your test case or suite.

    Can be used with a RegisterExtension field. If used with a class static field then use setClassLevel(true) to create contained Executor instance only once for all tests in class.

      • withTestExecutor

        public static ExecutorExtension<TestExecutor> withTestExecutor()
        Create an ExecutorExtension with a TestExecutor.

        executor() will return the TestExecutor to allow controlling the executor in tests.

        The TestExecutor is designed to be used for a single test and should not be shared. Specifically, it is generally incompatible with setClassLevel(true).

        Returns:
        a new ExecutorExtension.
